  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <dl>
    <dt>What makes this different from other SEO tools?</dt>
    <dd>Booltools SEO Crawler is 100% free, open-source, and includes 24 GEO (Generative Engine Optimization) rules for AI search readiness that most paid tools don't cover. It also runs locally — your data never leaves your machine.</dd>
    <dt>Can I use it in my CI/CD pipeline?</dt>
    <dd>Yes. The SDK is a standalone binary that exits with code 1 when issues are found above your configured threshold. It's available as a <a href="https://github.com/marketplace/actions/booltools-seo-crawler">GitHub Action</a> on the Marketplace.</dd>
    <dt>Does it support JavaScript-rendered pages?</dt>
    <dd>The crawler fetches server-rendered HTML. For SPAs that rely on client-side rendering, use the static mode with your pre-built output directory, or crawl against a running dev server.</dd>
    <dt>How many pages can it crawl?</dt>
    <dd>By default up to 1,000 pages per domain. You can increase this with the <code>--max-pages</code> flag or the web UI settings. The crawler respects robots.txt and rate-limits itself to avoid overloading target servers.</dd>
  </dl>

